      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right to scrutinize fillers; simpler, whole-food ingredients are always preferable to cheap fillers. If your lab is still quite active, a little fat is crucial for energy, so don't fear all fat, but prioritize quality sources like fish oil or lean meats. Generally, opting for better ingredients is an investment against future health issues, which is often more valuable than saving a few dollars now. A high-quality, moderately priced food with recognizable ingredients is usually the sweet spot.",
      "source": "target",
