    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the info. one more thing, i've heard some people say that raw diets or \"ancestral\" feeding can be better for their digestion, but it seems like a lot of work to get the proportions right for an older dog. is there a specific way i should be looking at the calorie density per cup to make sure he doesn't balloon in size?",
